	<!-- explosives -->
	<element name="Bomb" type="Item" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_ITEM_BOMB">
        <supports>ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AVAILABILITY_MERCHANT</supports>
		<description>
			<p>A bomb is a unadorned sphere of thin iron designed to disintegrate when the powder inside it detonates. As an action, you may place the bomb on the ground or throw it up to 20 feet. Bombs do not go off immediately, instead exploding at the beginning of your next turn. Anyone within a 5-foot radius of the bomb when it detonates takes 2d6 fire damage and 2d6 piercing damage, or half as much damage on a successful DC 13 Dexterity save.</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Explosives</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">150</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="1">1 lb.</set>
			<set name="stackable">true</set>
		</setters>
	</element>
	<element name="Gunpowder, Powder Horn" type="Item" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_ITEM_GUNPOWDER_POWDER_HORN">
        <supports>ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AVAILABILITY_MERCHANT</supports>
		<description>
			<p>Often hung on a leather strap for easy portability, a gunpowder horn holds up to 100 doses of gunpowder. Groups using the rules for simple ammunition crafting do not need to worry about gunpowder.</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Explosives</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">35</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="2">2 lb.</set>
			<set name="stackable">true</set>
		</setters>
	</element>
	<element name="Gunpowder, Keg" type="Item" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_ITEM_GUNPOWDER_KEG">
        <supports>ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AVAILABILITY_MERCHANT</supports>
		<description>
			<p>Less portable than a horn, a gunpowder keg holds up to 1000 doses of gunpowder and is often transported via horse or wagon. Groups using the rules for simple ammunition crafting do not need to worry about gunpowder.</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Explosives</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">250</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="20">20 lb.</set>
			<set name="stackable">true</set>
		</setters>
	</element>
    
	<element name="Buckshot" type="Item" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_ITEM_BUCKSHOT">
        <supports>ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AVAILABILITY_MERCHANT</supports>
		<description>
			<p>A package of small lead pellets that scatter when fired, doing damage to creatures in a large area.</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Ammunition</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="sp">4</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="0.1">1/10 lb.</set>
			<set name="stackable">true</set>
		</setters>
	</element>
	<element name="Cartridge" type="Item" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_ITEM_CARTRIDGE">
        <supports>ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AVAILABILITY_MERCHANT</supports>
		<description>
			<p>A bullet and dose of powder are combined within a package of stiff, chemically treated paper to form a cartridge. The paper and powder burn away when fired, sending the bullet forward on its own. If your group is using the rules for simple ammunition crafting, the terms cartridge and bullet may be used interchangeably, and you should use the statistics for cartridges for bullets.</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Ammunition</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="sp">4</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="0.1">1/10 lb.</set>
			<set name="stackable">true</set>
		</setters>
	</element>
	<element name="Concussive Cartridge (Alchemical)" type="Item" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_ITEM_CONCUSSIVE_CARTRIDGE">
        <supports></supports>
		<description>
			<p>Concussive cartridges deal an additional 2d6 thunder damage when they hit a target. Like explosive cartridges, they are volatile and prone to failure—the Misfire score of a firearm is temporarily raised by 2 for a shot made using an concussive cartridge. Such ammunition cannot usually be bought from merchants, and must be handmade.</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Ammunition</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">25</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="0.1">1/10 lb.</set>
			<set name="stackable">true</set>
		</setters>
	</element>
	<element name="Explosive Cartridge (Alchemical)" type="Item" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_ITEM_EXPLOSIVE_CARTRIDGE">
        <supports></supports>
		<description>
			<p>For important shots or simply more firepower, explosive cartridges deal an additional 2d6 fire damage when they hit a target. Their volatility, however, makes them prone to failure—the Misfire score of a firearm is temporarily raised by 2 for a shot made using an explosive cartridge. Such ammunition cannot usually be bought from merchants, and must be handmade.</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Ammunition</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">25</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="0.1">1/10 lb.</set>
			<set name="stackable">true</set>
		</setters>
	</element>
	<element name="Musketball" type="Item" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_ITEM_MUSKETBALL">
        <supports>ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AVAILABILITY_MERCHANT</supports>
		<description>
			<p>A simple ball of lead, paired with a dose of black powder when loaded into a firearm. Although the ball and powder are technically two separate items, they’re mechanically treated as one for the sake of simplicity.</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Ammunition</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="sp">2</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="0.1">1/10 lb.</set>
			<set name="stackable">true</set>
		</setters>
	</element>

	<element name="Arquebus" type="Weapon" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_ARQUEBUS">
		<supports>ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_FIREARM, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_MARTIAL_RANGED, ID_INTERNAL_DAMAGE_TYPE_PIERCING, ID_WOTC_DMG_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AMMUNITION, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_LOADING,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_RELOAD,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_MISFIRE,ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_TWOHANDED,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AVAILABILITY_MERCHANT,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_COMPLEXITY_BASIC</supports>
		<description>
            <p>The most basic combination of barrel, stock, and trigger, arquebuses use actual burning matches to set off their powder charge. This makes them cumbersome to use and load, but also cheap to produce, and therefore quite common.</p>
        </description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Weapons</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">200</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="12">12 lb.</set>
			<set name="slot">twohand</set>
			<set name="range">30/90</set>
			<set name="damage" type="piercing">1d10</set>
			<set name="proficiency">ID_FRL_GPC_PROFICIENCY_WEAPON_ARQUEBUS</set>
            <set name="reload">1</set>
			<!-- <set name="ammunition">ID_WOTC_DMG_ITEM_BULLET</set> -->
		</setters>
	</element>
	<element name="Flintlock Pistol" type="Weapon" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_FLINTLOCK_PISTOL">
		<supports>ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_FIREARM, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_MARTIAL_RANGED, ID_INTERNAL_DAMAGE_TYPE_PIERCING, ID_WOTC_DMG_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AMMUNITION, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_LOADING,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_RELOAD,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_MISFIRE,ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_LIGHT,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AVAILABILITY_MERCHANT,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_COMPLEXITY_BASIC</supports>
		<description>
            <p>The first kind of pistol that didn’t require using an actual match, these are muzzle-loading, single-shot pistols. They are simple to build and perhaps the most common firearm around.</p>
        </description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Weapons</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">150</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="2">2 lb.</set>
			<set name="slot">onehand</set>
			<set name="range">15/60</set>
			<set name="damage" type="piercing">1d8</set>
			<set name="proficiency">ID_FRL_GPC_PROFICIENCY_WEAPON_FLINTLOCK_PISTOL</set>
            <set name="reload">1</set>
			<!-- <set name="ammunition">ID_WOTC_DMG_ITEM_BULLET</set> -->
		</setters>
	</element>
	<element name="Musket" type="Weapon" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_MUSKET">
		<supports>ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_FIREARM, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_MARTIAL_RANGED, ID_INTERNAL_DAMAGE_TYPE_PIERCING, ID_WOTC_DMG_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AMMUNITION, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_LOADING,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_RELOAD,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_MISFIRE,ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_TWOHANDED,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AVAILABILITY_MERCHANT,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_COMPLEXITY_BASIC</supports>
		<description>
            <p>A step up from an arquebus, a musket is a flintlock weapon that uses steel on flint to set off the powder. It is still slow to load, but has slightly better range, packs more of a punch, and weighs less.</p>
        </description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Weapons</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">750</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="10">10 lb.</set>
			<set name="slot">twohand</set>
			<set name="range">40/120</set>
			<set name="damage" type="piercing">1d12</set>
			<set name="proficiency">ID_FRL_GPC_PROFICIENCY_WEAPON_MUSKET</set>
            <set name="reload">1</set>
			<!-- <set name="ammunition">ID_WOTC_DMG_ITEM_BULLET</set> -->
		</setters>
	</element>
	<element name="Pocket Pistol" type="Weapon" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_POCKET_PISTOL">
		<supports>ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_FIREARM, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_MARTIAL_RANGED, ID_INTERNAL_DAMAGE_TYPE_PIERCING, ID_WOTC_DMG_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AMMUNITION, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_LOADING,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_RELOAD,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_MISFIRE,ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_LIGHT,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_COVERT,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AVAILABILITY_MERCHANT,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_COMPLEXITY_BASIC</supports>
		<description>
            <p>A gentleman’s weapon, pocket pistols are basic flintlock weapons designed to be easily hidden. They are, however, notably unreliable and short range.</p>
        </description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Weapons</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">125</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="1">1 lb.</set>
			<set name="slot">onehand</set>
			<set name="range">10/40</set>
			<set name="damage" type="piercing">1d8</set>
			<set name="proficiency">ID_FRL_GPC_PROFICIENCY_WEAPON_POCKET_PISTOL</set>
            <set name="reload">1</set>
			<!-- <set name="ammunition">ID_WOTC_DMG_ITEM_BULLET</set> -->
		</setters>
	</element>
	<element name="Scattergun" type="Weapon" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_SCATTERGUN">
		<supports>ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_FIREARM, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_MARTIAL_RANGED, ID_INTERNAL_DAMAGE_TYPE_PIERCING, ID_WOTC_DMG_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AMMUNITION, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_LOADING,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_RELOAD,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_MISFIRE,ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_TWOHANDED,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_SCATTER,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AVAILABILITY_MERCHANT,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_COMPLEXITY_BASIC</supports>
		<description>
            <p>Scatterguns are similar to muskets in that they are muzzle-loaded and must be reloaded after each shot. They are similarly flintlock weapons, but instead of a single ball they fire buckshot—a grouping of tiny pellets that spread out over a wide area.</p>
        </description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Weapons</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">500</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="10">10 lb.</set>
			<set name="slot">onehand</set>
			<set name="range">15/30</set>
			<set name="damage" type="piercing">1d8</set>
			<set name="proficiency">ID_FRL_GPC_PROFICIENCY_WEAPON_SCATTERGUN</set>
            <set name="reload">1</set>
			<!-- <set name="ammunition">ID_WOTC_DMG_ITEM_BULLET</set> -->
		</setters>
	</element>

	<element name="Double Hunting Rifle" type="Weapon" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_DOUBLE_HUNTING_RIFLE">
		<supports>ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_ADVANCED_FIREARM, ID_INTERNAL_DAMAGE_TYPE_PIERCING, ID_WOTC_DMG_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AMMUNITION, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_LOADING,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_RELOAD,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_MISFIRE</supports>
		<description>
            <p>A hunting rifle with two barrels, one stacked atop the other.</p>
        </description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Weapons</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">3500</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="10">10 lb.</set>
			<set name="slot">onehand</set>
			<set name="range">100/400</set>
			<set name="damage" type="piercing">2d10</set>
			<set name="proficiency">ID_FRL_GPC_PROFICIENCY_WEAPON_ADVANCED_DOUBLE_HUNTING_RIFLE</set>
            <set name="reload">2</set>
			<set name="misfire">2</set>
			<!-- <set name="ammunition">ID_WOTC_DMG_ITEM_BULLET</set> -->
		</setters>
	</element>
	<element name="Gatling Gun" type="Weapon" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_GATLING_GUN">
		<supports>ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_ADVANCED_FIREARM, ID_INTERNAL_DAMAGE_TYPE_PIERCING, ID_WOTC_DMG_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AMMUNITION, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_LOADING,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_RELOAD,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_MISFIRE</supports>
		<description>
            <p>A large, lever-cranked weapon that can be fired rapidly, gatling guns are usually mounted on wagons or carried via complicated leather harnesses. They are exceedingly intricate and expensive to build, making them rare finds in most locations.</p>
        </description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Weapons</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">7500</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="20">20 lb.</set>
			<set name="slot">onehand</set>
			<set name="range">30/90</set>
			<set name="damage" type="piercing">2d8</set>
			<set name="proficiency">ID_FRL_GPC_PROFICIENCY_WEAPON_ADVANCED_GATLING_GUN</set>
            <set name="reload">40</set>
			<set name="misfire">3</set>
			<!-- <set name="ammunition">ID_WOTC_DMG_ITEM_BULLET</set> -->
		</setters>
	</element>
	<element name="Harmonica Gun" type="Weapon" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_HARMONICA_GUN">
		<supports>ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_ADVANCED_FIREARM, ID_INTERNAL_DAMAGE_TYPE_PIERCING, ID_WOTC_DMG_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AMMUNITION, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_LOADING,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_RELOAD,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_MISFIRE</supports>
		<description>
            <p>A harmonica gun is breech-loaded with a steel slide, containing a number of chambers bored in it which are filled with cartridges. As you fire each shot, you push the slide through a bit to line up the next cartridge. An intricate design, these are rare sights in most areas.</p>
        </description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Weapons</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">3000</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="3">3 lb.</set>
			<set name="slot">onehand</set>
			<set name="range">40/120</set>
			<set name="damage" type="piercing">2d6</set>
			<set name="proficiency">ID_FRL_GPC_PROFICIENCY_WEAPON_ADVANCED_HARMONICA_GUN</set>
            <set name="reload">9</set>
			<set name="misfire">2</set>
			<!-- <set name="ammunition">ID_WOTC_DMG_ITEM_BULLET</set> -->
		</setters>
	</element>
	<element name="Howdah Pistol" type="Weapon" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_HOWDAH_PISTOL">
		<supports>ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_ADVANCED_FIREARM, ID_INTERNAL_DAMAGE_TYPE_PIERCING, ID_WOTC_DMG_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AMMUNITION, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_LOADING,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_RELOAD,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_MISFIRE</supports>
		<description>
            <p>Designed specifically for killing large game, howdah pistols are large-caliber handguns that pack a wallop. They are breech-loaded but single-shot, trading capacity for power.</p>
        </description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Weapons</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">2000</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="4">4 lb.</set>
			<set name="slot">onehand</set>
			<set name="range">60/200</set>
			<set name="damage" type="piercing">2d10</set>
			<set name="proficiency">ID_FRL_GPC_PROFICIENCY_WEAPON_ADVANCED_HOWDAH_PISTOL</set>
            <set name="reload">1</set>
			<set name="misfire">2</set>
			<!-- <set name="ammunition">ID_WOTC_DMG_ITEM_BULLET</set> -->
		</setters>
	</element>
	<element name="Hunting Rifle" type="Weapon" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_HUNTING_RIFLE">
		<supports>ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_ADVANCED_FIREARM, ID_INTERNAL_DAMAGE_TYPE_PIERCING, ID_WOTC_DMG_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AMMUNITION, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_LOADING,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_RELOAD,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_MISFIRE</supports>
		<description>
            <p>More sophisticated than a musket, a hunting rifle is a breech-loader and fires cartridges. Its long range makes it popular with hunters and marksmen, although they are not as common or cheap as muskets or arquebuses.</p>
        </description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Weapons</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">3000</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="9">9 lb.</set>
			<set name="slot">onehand</set>
			<set name="range">100/400</set>
			<set name="damage" type="piercing">2d10</set>
			<set name="proficiency">ID_FRL_GPC_PROFICIENCY_WEAPON_ADVANCED_HUNTING_RIFLE</set>
            <set name="reload">1</set>
			<set name="misfire">2</set>
			<!-- <set name="ammunition">ID_WOTC_DMG_ITEM_BULLET</set> -->
		</setters>
	</element>
	<element name="Lever-Action Rifle" type="Weapon" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_LEVER_ACTION_RIFLE">
		<supports>ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_ADVANCED_FIREARM, ID_INTERNAL_DAMAGE_TYPE_PIERCING, ID_WOTC_DMG_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AMMUNITION, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_LOADING,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_RELOAD,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_MISFIRE</supports>
		<description>
            <p>The rare product of master gunsmiths, lever-action rifles keep extra rounds in a tubular magazine under the barrel, and each new cartridge is loaded by using the lever that’s part of the trigger guard. They are intricate and difficult to build, making them prized possessions of those lucky enough to own one.</p>
        </description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Weapons</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">7000</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="8">8 lb.</set>
			<set name="slot">onehand</set>
			<set name="range">80/240</set>
			<set name="damage" type="piercing">2d8</set>
			<set name="proficiency">ID_FRL_GPC_PROFICIENCY_WEAPON_ADVANCED_LEVER_ACTION_RIFLE</set>
            <set name="reload">15</set>
			<set name="misfire">2</set>
			<!-- <set name="ammunition">ID_WOTC_DMG_ITEM_BULLET</set> -->
		</setters>
	</element>
	<element name="Pepperbox" type="Weapon" source="The Gunpowder Codex" id="ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PEPPERBOX">
		<supports>ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_CATEGORY_ADVANCED_FIREARM, ID_INTERNAL_DAMAGE_TYPE_PIERCING, ID_WOTC_DMG_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AMMUNITION, ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_LOADING,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_RELOAD,ID_FRL_GPC_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_MISFIRE</supports>
		<description>
            <p>The simplest method to fire multiple shots without reloading is to have more barrels, as a pepperbox does. All four barrels rotate together to line up the next barrel with the hammer.</p>
        </description>
		<setters>
			<set name="category">Weapons</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">1000</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="4">4 lb.</set>
			<set name="slot">onehand</set>
